>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Vox July 24th (Time changed, Possibly canceled)</span><hr size=1> Due to the MASSIVE difficulty a ton of people are having in logging on, I'm post-poning this raid until later tonight. If a Vox raid has not already formed, I will move in with the rules I have set up here, and lead. However, the server will most likely go down again soon. (It is 2pm est now) I do not want to end up rushing a raid, or even have the servers die at the wrong time.<br>
<br>
<br>
Thank you for signing up, I hope some of you are on later tonight when VI gets things sorted out.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   Original Message:</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>             From EQlive:</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>             On Wednesday, July 24th, at 3AM PDT, (10AM GMT), all EverQuest servers will be brought down for a scheduled patch. The estimated downtime is 5 hours. The EverQuest Operations Team<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I plan on leading a Vox raid on the 24th. The servers go down at 3am pst for 5 hours. They are estimated to be back up at 8am pst. I'm planning on starting this raid at <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>             3pm EST.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    The Specs</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>    Time:</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->Be IN Permafrost by 3pm est<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>    Levels:</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->You must be 45th season or above to attend this raid.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>    Dots:</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->Will be provided/reimbursed. I will provide dots, and will reimburse depending on how many people turn out that did NOT sign up on this page.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>    Wizards/Portal Fragments:</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> I will provide each wizard that attends the raid with one stack of Portal Fragments from the temple of Solusek Ro. These should provide plenty of teleports for everyone.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>             Loot:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>             <br>
Book - Paladins 50+ (Sorry lower level guys)<br>
<br>
Scale - Bards 50+<br>
<br>
RBB - All Melees that attend (No, a bard is not a melee)<br>
<br>
Bracer - Monk / Rog<br>
<br>
Spear - Rogue<br>
<br>
Bag - The Bag will be randomed to anyone interested, assuming no monk has a Tink Bag to trade in. If there is more than one monk with a tink bag, I will do a random between them to decide who gets the trade in.<br>
<br>
Rez Sticks - Reserving for my guild, Of the sword.<br>
<br>
Eye Patch - All Casters<br>
<br>
Ice Comet - Any wizard that needs it, otherwise it will go into my guild bank.<br>
<br>
Hammer - Cleric<br>
<br>
Horn - Bard<br>
<br>
If for some reason there is an item that none of the reserved classes wants, it will be randomed/given to anyone who wants it.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>        Resists</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Please have your sv magic AT LEAST 60, unbuffed. Your sv cold should be 80, unbuffed. Granted you want the HIGHEST possible sv cold and magic, these are the bare minimum to survive and actually help the raid. <br>
<br>
Casters SHOULD trade in int/wis/mana for saves!<br>
<br>
Melees SHOULD trade in ac for saves.<br>
<br>
It is crucial that you have decent resists in order to survive this raid. Here are some suggestons on gear, along with prices:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>        Velium Diamond Wedding ring 8sv ALL Ring, roughly 500pp ea from a Jeweler.<br>
<br>
Crown of the Frogluk kings (10sv cold / 10sv fire) rougly 1000pp<br>
<br>
Cloak of the Ice Bear (20sv cold) roughly 100pp<br>
<br>
</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
These are by all means small suggestions, with just these how ever, your sv cold would go up 38. <br>
<br>
Merely suggestions, please have SOME sv gear if you plan on attending this raid. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>        Strategy Discussion</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Bards: Bards will mana sieve Vox, and run resist songs. After Vox is looted, the groups will disband, and all bards will group with all clerics to assist with Rezs. <br>
<br>
Beastlord: I have not had much experience with this class, as far as I am concerned, Melee yer asses off.<br>
<br>
Cleric: Clerics will make sure that the tank in their group stays healed. Clerics will NOT heal themselves, unless there is a lack of back up healers and paladins. <br>
<br>
Druid: Back up healer. The cleric's job is to keep the tank healed, the druid's job is to make sure the cleric and other classes in the group stay healed.<br>
<br>
Enchanter: The enchanter will wait for the call, and cast Tash on Vox. If Vox does not eat you after Tash lands, your job is to mana sieve.<br>
<br>
Magician: Deal damage<br>
<br>
Monk: Deal damage<br>
<br>
Necromancer: Necros will NOT DOT. They fixed the issue with dots rotting corpses, how ever this does not mean I want you to dot. Necros will mana feed the clerics. <br>
<br>
Paladin: STUN, paladins will STUN their asses off when I give the call. (This will end up being between 20% and 50% health). You can not stun Vox to make her stop her melee, how ever, if your stun lands, there is a chance it will interrupt her casting. The paladin, if grouped with a cleric, will take it upon themselves to use LoH on the cleric if his hp gets low enough to need it.<br>
<br>
Ranger: Melee / Damage dealer<br>
<br>
Rogue: Deal damage<br>
<br>
Shadow Knight: At 30% health, use your harmtouch. <br>
<br>
Shaman: Debuffs on Vox<br>
<br>
Warrior: Taunt, taunt, taunt. <br>
<br>
Wizard: Deal massive amounts of damage. Upon Vox reaching 30% health, UNLOAD. You will not use your stuns on Vox. You will be trying to deal AS MUCH DAMAGE AS POSSIBLE, within her 30% life. This is where she casts her horrible CH, we need to have her killed before she gets it off.<br>
<br>
Various:<br>
Vox is a level 55 dragon who can melee up to 250. (Up to) She will resist all spells cast on her, unless you are in melee range. For casters, this is best off IN HER BELLY. Fire based spells work best on her.<br>
<br>
Upon coming back from the chat room, we will regroup. Once the first charge is called, everyone with the Resist disc will use it. Warriors ONLY will then rush Vox. Upon the second call of charge, MELEES only will rush. Upon the 3rd call, all the casters will rush Vox. If a healer notices a group member getting the crap kicked out of them prior to the caster charge, they CAN run in and heal the injured. <br>
<br>
There are pits in Vox's room. If you're new to Vox, follow everyone else and do NOT wander off. You will be fine. If you do fall in the pit, we will have coffins to retrieve your corpse.<br>
<br>
If Vox for some reason gets to a wall, we will lose. There is no way to finish the raid at that point. She will get in the wall, and summon each person, one by one and eat them. We MUST position her AWAY from the walls.<br>
<br>
The chat channel that will be used for this raid is going to be:<br>
<br>
/join Helius:vox<br>
<br>
Please come prepared, and we will have no trouble.<br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
If in the event of a very bad wipe out, I will provide coffins, assuming we have a necro capable of summoning corpses.<br>
<br>
These are my rules, if you do not feel they fit to you, please do not attend. <br>
<br>
If you are above the 52nd level, and interested in helping with the Ice Giants or the Buff Hall, please shoot me a tell in game and we can have a little chat. If you have a 52+ alt that is capable of buffing, please add that in with your post.<br>
<br>
I hope this gives verant enough time to run any emergency patches that they may need to follow up after the new UI goes live. If for some reason the server is called to go down mid raid (before we camp to chat) we will NOT rush. The last raid I did, we rushed Vox with 10 minutes before the servers went down. We killed her, got the loot, and got as many corpses out as possible. There were a few people who did not get rezs. That was not an easy CR, and it is not going to happen again with me. I will not r ush this raid for the sake of two Voxs.<br>
<br>
